===Noun===
'''prang'''
#(UK slang)  A car [[crash]], [[accident]] without any casualties, typically minor; as in (US) [[fender-bender]]. (Believed to have originated in the [[RAF]] during WW2).
#Meaning to get paranoid about something (be in a state of paranoia).
#Synonym for crack cocaine
#(Chiefly NZ) .

===Verb===
'''to prang'''
#to [[crash]], to have an [[accident]]